column31: My sister lays in a hospital bed, legs outstretched and filled with so much fluid they pit when you press on them. The pressure of the constant fluid has caused her knee caps to crumble. She can barely walk, and she can’t hold her head up for long. She doesn’t have #coronavirus. She isn’t even in a hospital. But she is one of the 133 million Americans currently living with a chronic health condition. It is estimated that 60% of Americans have at least one chronic condition, and 40% have two or more. It’s not just adults. The percent of children living with a chronic health condition ranges from 27% of children have a condition that affects their daily activities, to 54% of children have a chronic health condition when overweight, obesity, or being at risk for developmental delays are included. These numbers are rising, and there is no genetic explanation: asthma and Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD) rates are disproportionately higher for children living in poverty, compared to wealthier families, and a recent study found Autism is half as common in wealthy whites compared to poor whites living in the same exact State. "There is an urgent need to understand what wealthy California parents are doing or have access to that may be lowering their children’s risk, and what changes occurred around 2000 that may have affected these parents’ behavior or options. Conversely, there is an equally urgent need to understand the factors that may lead to increased risk of ASD among lower income populations, including factors that may be beyond their control, such as access to and autonomy over healthy food, health care, stressful environments and toxic exposures." These studies suggest what many of us have known for a long time: genetics don’t cause epidemics. The truth is, wealthy whites are avoiding or opting out of many of the possible environmental triggers that compromise our children’s health, and rob them of their full potential. Some of the medications and vaccines given for free through Medicaid may be fundamentally different as well. Either way, it’s not the parent’s fault when they too are just ‘following doctor’s orders’. And everything, from infant formula to vaccinations, is FDA approved. We have been failed by these regulatory agencies. *This* is the news story. 🇺🇸 In the United States: 🇺🇸 1,773 people die of heart disease every single day 1,641 people die of cancer every single day 438 people die of chronic lower respiratory diseases every single day 332 people die of Alzheimer’s disease every single day These major causes of death take the lives of 1.5 million people every single year. Where are all the news stories? These people are not just numbers–they are grandmas and grandpas, aunts and uncles, mothers and fathers, and children. About 16,000 children 18 years and under will be diagnosed with cancer this year alone, an unexplained increase of 60% over the last 41 years. The causes of many of these chronic conditions often hide behind the ambivalent “unknown cause.” But I have a feeling, we could figure it out if we really tried. We do know that many of them have environmental causes: diet, air pollution, water quality, pesticides, chemicals, sunscreens, beauty products, medications and vaccines–all contribute something to the toxic load. For example, children who receive ‘any vaccines’ are about 2.4 times more likely to have any chronic condition, compared to completely unvaccinated children. My sister. After decades of losing battle after battle with her weight (unhealthy eating habits, fast food, big gulps, fried food—these are ‘classic American staples’ right?) and she was and is a smoker too, my sister had an early form of the gastric bypass surgery, the Roux-en-Y gastric bypass, which removed most of her small intestine. The exact surgery she had, they don’t do anymore, it is so dangerous to one’s health. The FDA approved surgery thrust her into a state of malnutrition. She lost all her hair. One in 5 post-surgery patients develop alcohol problems, and she did. She ended up losing everything: her family, then her custody, her job, and her spark. Right when she started to get things together again, she developed a Deep Vein Thrombosis (DVT) in her leg. Her doctors recommended implanting an IVC filter (inferior vena cava filter) which is a little wire filter that resembles a long legged spider. It was placed in her major artery to catch the small blood clots that might break off the larger clot. It was only supposed to be temporary and she was also given blood thinners. (It’s supposed to be one or the other, not both). The doctor at the hospital who discharged her calculated her blood thinners wrong, and overdosed her. Within three days of being home they frantically searched for an OB/GYN who would perform an emergency hysterectomy to stop a pelvic bleed. column36:
Johns Hopkins University has sent this detailed note on avoiding the contagion:

* The virus is not a living organism, but a protein molecule (DNA) covered by a protective layer of lipid (fat), which, when absorbed by the cells of the ocular, nasal or buccal mucosa, changes their genetic code. (mutation) and convert them into aggressor and multiplier cells.

* Since the virus is not a living organism but a protein molecule, it is not killed, but decays on its own. The disintegration time depends on the temperature, humidity and type of material where it lies.

* The virus is very fragile; the only thing that protects it is a thin outer layer of fat. That is why any soap or detergent is the best remedy, because the foam CUTS the FAT (that is why you have to rub so much: for 20 seconds or more, to make a lot of foam). By dissolving the fat layer, the protein molecule disperses and breaks down on its own.

* HEAT melts fat; this is why it is so good to use water above 25 degrees Celsius for washing hands, clothes and everything. In addition, hot water makes more foam and that makes it even more useful.

* Alcohol or any mixture with alcohol over 65% DISSOLVES ANY FAT, especially the external lipid layer of the virus.

* Any mix with 1 part bleach and 5 parts water directly dissolves the protein, breaks it down from the inside.

* Oxygenated water helps long after soap, alcohol and chlorine, because peroxide dissolves the virus protein, but you have to use it pure and it hurts your skin.

* NO BACTERICIDE SERVES. The virus is not a living organism like bacteria; they cannot kill what is not alive with anthobiotics, but quickly disintegrate its structure with everything said.

* NEVER shake used or unused clothing, sheets or cloth. While it is glued to a porous surface, it is very inert and disintegrates only between 3 hours (fabric and porous), 4 hours (copper, because it is naturally antiseptic; and wood, because it removes all the moisture and does not let it peel off and disintegrates). ), 24 hours (cardboard), 42 hours (metal) and 72 hours (plastic). But if you shake it or use a feather duster, the virus molecules float in the air for up to 3 hours, and can lodge in your nose.

* The virus molecules remain very stable in external cold, or artificial as air conditioners in houses and cars. They also need moisture to stay stable, and especially darkness. Therefore, dehumidified, dry, warm and bright environments will degrade it faster.

* UV LIGHT on any object that may contain it breaks down the virus protein. For example, to disinfect and reuse a mask is perfect. Be careful, it also breaks down collagen (which is protein) in the skin, eventually causing wrinkles and skin cancer.

* The virus CANNOT go through healthy skin.

* Vinegar is NOT useful because it does not break down the protective layer of fat.

* NO SPIRITS, NOR VODKA, serve. The strongest vodka is 40% alcohol, and you need 65%.

* LISTERINE IF IT SERVES! It is 65% alcohol.

* The more confined the space, the more concentration of the virus there can be. The more open or naturally ventilated, the less.

* This is super said, but you have to wash your hands before and after touching mucosa, food, locks, knobs, switches, remote control, cell phone, watches, computers, desks, TV, etc. And when using the bathroom.

* You have to HUMIDIFY HANDS DRY from so much washing them, because the molecules can hide in the micro cracks. The thicker the moisturizer, the better.

* Also keep your NAILS SHORT so that the virus does not hide there.

column31: As we have watched the world's response to coronavirus, we have wondered why several other countries seemed to have accurate, rapid testing methods that were readily available, while the US didn't. Here's why: "...enabled researchers in Berlin to develop a test to detect infections in just six days. This is what we now use to track infected people around the world—except in the U.S., where the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention insisted on keeping it out and developing a domestic, faulty test, which set back American efforts several weeks." It seems that most countries shared science and data and developments, which enabled them to respond more quickly to what was happening, isolating the people who were actually sick or had been exposed. But the CDC *refused* to listen to anyone else, and instead insisted on developing a test that took weeks longer to create, isn't that accurate, and still isn't readily available. That, plus a bungled projection of the oncoming damage, led to all the shut-downs we're currently facing. We're supposed to trust them, after their poor response to this situation?

column31: US autism rates up 10 percent in new CDC report. Since 2000, prevalence rate has nearly tripled, from 0.67 to 1.85 percent. Consistent with previous reports, boys were 4 to 5 times more likely to be identified with ASD than girls. The rate for ASD is 1 in 34 among boys (or 2.97 percent) and 1 in 145 among girls (or 0.69 percent). This is the seventh report by the ADDM Network, which has used the same surveillance methods each time. Estimated prevalence rates of ASD in the U.S. reported by previous data were: one in 59 children in the 2018 report based on 2014 data one in 68 children in the 2016 report based on 2012 data one in 68 children in the 2014 report based on 2010 data one in 88 children in the 2012 report based on 2008 data one in 110 children in the 2009 report based on 2006 data one in 150 children in the 2007 report based on 2000 and 2002 data

column31: Another gift to industry that could negatively affect the health of everyone and especially children. On 3/11 Congress passed S.893. On 3/23 Trump signed it into law and on 3/25 the White House quietly published the policy paper required by the Act. The policy paper outlines four distinct lines of effort that the bill called for it to include. They each lay out the administration’s approaches and aims to: (1) facilitate the domestic rollout of 5G; (2) assess the risks and identify the core security principles of 5G infrastructure; (3) assess the risks to United States economic and national security during development and deployment of 5G infrastructure worldwide, (4) and promote responsible global development and deployment of 5G. The 7 page policy paper is here: https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/National-Strategy-5G-Final.pdf

column31: The telecom industry doesn't lose any opportunity to make money from data mining and increase its power while our rights are being trampled. column31: A NEW AUTISM STUDY using the CA DDS database has “unmasked” patterns showing that rates are evolving in strikingly different ways for different groups. Racial/ethnic minorities and lower-income families are increasingly bearing the brunt of severe autism, while conversely, ASD prevalence is flattening and even declining among whites in CA’s wealthier counties. African American children in CA had the highest ASD prevalence of any group, followed by Asian children. The analysis shows that parents armed with wealth, resources, education and access to information are succeeding in lowering their children’s risk for severe autism. The authors argue that “there is an urgent need to understand what [these] wealthy California parents are doing or have access to that may be lowering their children’s risk.” More soberly, there is also “an equally urgent need to understand the factors that may lead to increased risk of ASD among lower income populations”—and to ensure that low-income children benefit from the same protections as their wealthier counterparts. column31: We are in uncertain times right now. Many families have been ordered to "shelter in place." Many are out of work. Some are sick; a few, unfortunately, very sick. We are based out of Ohio, one of the states that has told people to stay at home. However, because we provide wellness and personal care products, we are considered an "essential business" and will remain open. We are taking some measures to help keep our staff, and our customers, safe. First, we are suspending local pick ups temporarily so we don't have any extra people in our building. Second, our staff members who do not have to come to work or are not comfortable doing so are staying at home. We of course ask any staff member who isn't feeling well to stay home as well. Fewer than 10 staff members are in the building at any time, and those who are there are washing hands frequently and maintaining social distance. We believe in our immune systems, and everyone has access to our immune-supporting products to help them stay healthy right now. We want to continue to be here for you during these difficult times. As long as our staff remains healthy, our doors will be open so that clean, safe products are available to ship to your door. Finally, a sobering note on all of the loss of freedom. While we support common-sense measures to keep people safe, we are astounded at how far things have gone in some areas. Many people have found themselves out of work, unable to travel, and facing potential homelessness in time. That's a big deal, too. We still stand for liberty, even in these difficult times. We wish everyone the best health and wellness.

column31: Coronavirus is causing a surge in unemployment rates. The relationship between unemployment and all-cause mortality found that unemployment increased the risk of dying by 63%. column31: “Let food be thy medicine & medicine be thy food.” ~ Hippocrates These words, first spoken about 400 B.C., emphasize the importance of nutrition to prevent or cure disease. Never in our lifetime has this message been more important. It’s time to shift our gaze from a quick pill or shot & turn to real food to bolster our health from the inside out. When Dr. Price traveled the world in the 1930s, he found that the isolated indigenous people who ate their traditional diet of real, nutrient-dense food exhibited superior health. Those who began eating the “displacing foods of modern commerce” suffered from dental cavities, decay, & compromised health that they had never experienced before. What he observed nearly 100 years ago, remains true for us today. Real food still nourishes best. It doesn’t come in plastic packages w/ long lists of ingredients. 🙄 I’m talking we need to eat the real stuff like bone broth, eggs, liver, cheese, butter.... All delicious, nutrient-dense & body & health-building. ☺️ I’ve been eating the wise traditions way for 15+ years & I have never been healthier. This is why my mission is to keep learning about ancient food & lifestyle ways and to share the best of what I learn with you. 👍 For more on this subject, listen to Wise Traditions podcast #162 “A Wise Diet” wherever you get your podcasts. column31: What is grounding you right now? It feels like the world is whirling right now, doesn’t it? At times, I’m like “What dystopian movie was I plopped in?” 😳 In the middle of the uncertainty with the pandemic, we want to be informed but not overwhelmed. Cautious, but not paranoid. And we must work on managing stress which lowers our immunity, making us more vulnerable to illness. Here are 3 tools that help ground me—keeping me emotionally & physically steady—on the most unsteady, rollercoaster-like🎢days. They may help you also. 🌍 E A R T H - ⬇️ Reach down. Touch the ground, literally. Garden. Get your hands dirty. Feel the earth. From it, we cultivate the food we eat. We get the energy we need. We get a sense of our literal & figurative place in this world when we touch nature. ☁️ S K Y - ⬆️ Reach up. Pray. Look to God, the Creator, the Source, the Higher Power. Cast all your cares on this One who cares for you. We receive peace that passes understanding & a sense of security when we trust that although things may be out of OUR control, they are NEVER too much for God. 💨 B R E A T H E - ➡️ Reach out. Expand & fill your lungs. Inhale peace, patience, well-being. Exhale & empty them. Release stress, negativity, fear. Repeat 5-6 times when you find you are breathing shallowly. This simple practice serves to remind us that we are alive & resilient, strong enough to persevere & thrive. When I feel small & weak, these practices steady me, and, like leaning against the grand Sequoia, I gain balance and strength once again. Do these resonate with you?🥰

column31: Children’s Health Defense strongly supports the rights of individuals to make voluntary choices regarding vaccines. Lawsuits related to human rights in Europe can ultimately be heard in an international court, the European Court of Human Rights (ECHR). With the assistance of Senta Depuydt and the European Forum for Vaccine Vigilance, Children’s Health Defense submitted a “friend of the court” brief. The Grand Chamber is scheduled to have a public hearing on the case on April 30, 2020 in Strasbourg, France, assuming that pandemic measures do not postpone it. The CHD brief cites the Nuremberg Code and the 2005 UNESCO Declaration on Bioethics and Human Rights. It also touches on the lack of proven safety and efficacy, religious rights, conflicts of interest, discrimination, questionable science, censorship, risk of genomic change, risk of unintended genocide, and liability as critical concerns that strongly weigh against vaccine mandates. Read the brief using the link at the end of this article. To get FREE updates from CHD, go to: ChildrensHealthDefense.org/sign-up:=:https://ChildrensHealthDefense.org/about-us/sign-up/

column31: “If the listener could do ONE THING to improve their health, what would you recommend they do?” I’ve posed this question countless times on the Wise Traditions podcast! 🎧 And while in truth some answers take me by surprise, the majority are clear cut & extremely simple to put into action: ☀️ get outdoors & get that sun 🥣 eat nutrient dense foods 🏃🏻‍♀️ move 🥶 make your body work a bit 💧 sweat 😀 play 🛌 get a good night’s rest ❌ fast now & then 🙏 practice faith 🧡 connect w/ family & friends Does this list seem overwhelming or just right? Maybe your health hasn’t been a priority just yet. So pick one thing. (Just like I suggest on the podcast. ☺️) Start small & manageable. I started w/ faith 😊 & exercise. Then I added food. And so on. Here I’m barefoot hiking so I’m outside, moving, & getting sunshine all at once! Easy peasy Captain Breezy. 😁 What’s your story? Where did you start on your wellness journey? Or where do you plan to start? 🙂 Whatever you do, take action. Don’t let life or fear or circumstances just happen to you. Everyone can do ONE THING. P,S. Check out the Wise Traditions podcast wherever you get your podcasts. There’s bound to be at least one episode that speaks to you. 👍

column31: Right now, a coronavirus vaccine doesn't even exist. But scientists have actually been working to develop one since the mid-90s, and haven't been successful yet. It's rare for us to come right out and tell people what decision to make, but on this one -- we think caution is truly warranted, for the following reasons. 1. Inadequate Testing -- Since the world is essentially shutting down over this illness, and it's spreading much more widely than previous coronaviruses (albeit killing a much lower percentage), there is huge pressure to develop a vaccine. It likely will not go through the same level of testing that others do (which is already not enough). The high-risk population will be the test subjects, effectively. Be wary of anything that is essentially untested. 2. Previous vaccines have led to complications -- While animal models showed that vaccines in development appeared to work on very small groups, and claimed few to no short-term side effects, they also noticed an interesting thing. When animals were "challenged" with the virus after vaccination, they had scarring in the lungs. The outcome was, in some cases, worse than if they had just gotten the illness naturally. We don't know if a new vaccine would do that in humans, but we should certainly find out before releasing it widely. 3. Antigenic Drift -- Coronavirus is very similar to an adenovirus or influenza virus, in that it can mutate fairly rapidly. This means that people who have had it, can have it again (just a slightly different strain). So while people may become "immune" to the exact vaccine strain, it wouldn't prevent them from getting similar strains that have mutated as they went through the public. 4. Viral Shedding -- In previous vaccine trials, researchers noticed something else interesting. Vaccinated animals (intramuscular route) sometimes were shedding the virus in the days following vaccination, and *again* if they were challenged with the illness. This means that vaccinated people could actually become asymptomatic carriers and spread the disease to others. There are a LOT of issues here. A lot to be worked out. Rushing a vaccine to market isn't the best plan with this illness. Staying healthy by focusing on food and herbs is much safer, and it's available now. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15019110 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/m/pubmed/32133832/ https://thenativeantigencompany.com/coronaviruses-the-next-disease-x/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14676007 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/32106567

This pandemic is to be taken seriously. I’m also aware that this crisis may cause undo economic hardship to many. I’m going to keep my eyes peeled to see how I can personally help ease that stress. But I can’t help but wonder if it wouldn’t serve us to embrace (even just a tiny bit) this HUGE disruption to our home life, work, social gatherings, & travel. Many events & plans have been cancelled. All that I’ve listed in this picture & post have not. column31: We've seen a lot of people running around and claiming that 'this' herb is dangerous or 'that' herb is dangerous if you have CoVid-19. Mostly, that certain herbs will cause cytokine storms and kill you. If someone makes a claim like that, ask these questions: 1) How many people have died this way due to using this herb? Can you point to any cases? 2) What scientific evidence do you have that the herb unbalances pro-inflammatory cytokines and is a real risk? 3) What other documented evidence do you have that this herb can or has caused cytokine storms? The answer to #1 is almost certainly that they can't point to any cases because the risks are theoretical. The answer to #2 is usually a misinterpretation of the studies -- many show that while certain herbs increase pro-inflammatory cytokines, they *also* increase anti-inflammatory cytokines, creating balance. The answer to #3 is probably nothing. Alleging that a certain herb can literally kill you if used during a respiratory infection is very serious. No one should be making that claim unless they have solid evidence to back them up. It doesn't mean that some herbs won't be wrong for some people or situations -- they might. Certain herbs could, theoretically, worsen symptoms somewhat. People should listen to their bodies, and stop using anything that doesn't feel right. But these blanket, over-the-top claims need to stop. If we ever find solid evidence that an herb is dangerous (which is difficult right now because this strain is so new), we will absolutely change our recommendations and tell everyone the new information -- with the proper sources. Right now, although preemptive caution is warranted in some cases (such as for the elderly or those who are already very sick), we disagree that any specific should 'never' be used.

column31: Let's talk about pertussis! It's the next in our series, helping families feel completely informed about illness and the choices they have. :) Pertussis is actually pretty common in the US now, with thousands of cases occurring every year. It happens in both vaccinated and unvaccinated people quite commonly. For older children and adults, it's often minor, and simply an annoying cough. In very young children, especially babies, it can be serious. Babies under 3 months are most at risk. 1 out of 200 who are hospitalized, will die (on average). The vaccine is not a live bacteria, so it has an adjuvant added to it to stimulate an immune response. This adjuvant is aluminum hydroxide, which has been shown to get into brain tissue and can cause neurological damage. The vaccine's protection also wanes very rapidly. Some natural remedies for pertussis include high-dose vitamin C and mullein leaf tea or tincture. (We have an in-depth guide on our site if you want to know more!) Sources: https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/67/wr/mm6740a3.htm https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/pubs/pinkbook/pert.html https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4861987/ https://www.cdc.gov/pertu…/surv-reporting/cases-by-year.html https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519008/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20153253 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25428645 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26948677

column31: Lots of people are interested in natural remedies, but are wary because they "don't work." Some of that is just a lack of familiarity with herbs -- how can something we use for cooking be *that* powerful? But in other cases, it's actually due to one of these three mistakes. #1: Wrong Remedy Look online or in a group for a natural remedy for a health need, and you'll get many different answers. A lot of those are general remedies and may not be the right one for your specific needs. And if the remedy(ies) you choose aren't the right ones, well...they won't work! Imagine you have a headache, and someone advises you to use lavender EO to calm it, but the real reason if you haven't had enough water to drink. EOs aren't going to touch dehydration. Selecting the right remedy is important! #2: Waiting too Long Herbal remedies generally work by supporting the body's systems and helping them do their jobs. If the body is already sick, then it takes awhile for the remedies to help the body "gear up." In contrast, if symptoms have just started -- or if a family member is sick, and you might be next -- then the herbal remedies can shore up defenses *before* the illness really takes hold. They're going to work better if taken earlier. #3: Not Using Often Enough Taking a remedy once or twice when you remember isn't enough. Especially if you are really not feeling well, your body needs a lot of help. Many herbal remedies can and should be taken every 2 - 4 hours during the day, along with plenty of rest and fluids. Nourishing herbal teas and broths are good in between other remedies as well. If these three mistakes are corrected, herbs are powerful and amazing and can do wonders for health!

column31: "While not conclusive, the findings do spotlight potential signs of rare neurological harms that outside experts say warrant a comprehensive look at the raw data, and they paint a damning picture of how the manufacturers evaluated their products’ safety. Dr. Tom Jefferson, Jørgensen’s co-supervisor at the Nordic Cochrane Centre in Copenhagen, where the research was done, said safety was reported “higgledy-piggledy” in the 22 industry trials he and his colleagues examined. He added that the trials were “all at high risk of bias” and not “a fair test” of the vaccines." "What’s more, the manufacturers virtually always benchmarked Cervarix and Gardasil against licensed vaccines or proprietary vaccine ingredients known as aluminum adjuvants rather than against an inert saltwater placebo. This could mask potential side effects, Jørgensen and his colleagues argue, if the comparators turn out to carry risks of their own" "Regulators are not worried about the new review and have not changed any recommendations in response to it." "The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, for its part, declined to comment, citing “a long-standing tradition of not commenting on research or papers authored by those outside of CDC.” Conclusion: At 4 years follow-up, the HPV vaccines decreased HPV-related cancer precursors and treatment procedures but INCREASED serious nervous system disorders and general harms. For more information: see RFK, Jr's. Gardasil video on the clinical trials at: https://childrenshealthdefense.org/news/rfk-jr-video-and-facts-about-gardasil/

column31: The use of c-sections has been increasing worldwide over the last 30 years. In most developed countries, c-section rates now hover between 25 and 35% off all births (including 26% of low-risk births in the US). While the mainstream will say that c-sections are increasing because of the population of birthing women changing (older, heavier, with underlying health issues), this is largely not the case. More women are opting for *elective* c-sections because of the perception that they are, as one study put it, "...now an almost risk-free procedure…” According to other studies, women are choosing c-sections because friends recommended them, they're afraid of labor pain, they feel they won't have support for a natural birth, they don't want to lose control, and more. The perception is the problem. *Elective* c-sections are the riskiest of all births, especially when they occur prior to 39 weeks gestation. Both mothers and babies face significant morbidity, both at the time of birth, and in the years following. One Chinese study even showed that babies born via elective c-section were significantly more likely to have behavior problems in preschool! The perception that c-sections are "risk free" and simply another equal choice in birth must change. While c-sections are absolutely needed sometimes, they should be used in situations where there is medical need. Women who are considering opting for one need to have a complete and accurate risk profile in front of them, so they can make an informed decision. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4555060/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/30810436 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6332907/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6642781/ https://www.americashealthrankings.org/explore/health-of-women-and-children/measure/low_risk_cesarean/state/ALL

column31: The panic surrounding coronavirus is escalating daily. We want to put it into perspective. Everyone is nervous because no one is quite sure what is going on (if the news is telling the truth, etc.) and what will happen next. It's a new, uncertain situation, and "not knowing" is always the worst. That said, there are fewer than confirmed 500 cases in the US right now -- barely more than 1 in a million. Relatively few people are dying, and most are (unfortunately) elderly and in poor health. We face a lot of bigger risks, that affect us *everyday.* But we ignore them because they're always around and don't feel much like a threat. The sad truth is, *because* of most of the things on this list, some people will be more at risk of coronavirus than they should or need to be. And "economic downturn" is going to be caused by all the panic and preemptive shut-downs. The bottom line right now? If you are not feeling well, stay home. Wash your hands often. And take a hard look at these daily threats that we're ignoring that cause far more harm to our long-term health than coronavirus.

column31: Physicians for Informed Consent reanalyzed a 2011 FDA study and found a critical math error — which negates the FDA’s conclusion. The study looked at the safety of using aluminum in infant vaccines. The FDA paper assumed that nearly 8 times more aluminum can safely enter the bloodstream. Authors incorrectly concluded that aluminum exposure from vaccines was well below the safety limit: “episodic exposures to vaccines that contain aluminum adjuvant continue to be extremely low risk to infants and that the benefits of using vaccines containing aluminum adjuvant outweigh any theoretical concerns.” The paper with incorrect data has been quoted numerous times in the past 9 years to reassure parents regarding the safety of aluminum adjuvants.

column31: The Dunning-Krueger effect is interesting. Two researchers (Dunning and Krueger) asked a group of people to take a test, and then estimate how well they'd done on the test. Those who ended up with the lowest scores actually felt the most confident on their performance, while those with the top scores felt more unsure or even underestimated their performance. This led to the theory that some people are so ignorant/uneducated (at least on certain topics) that they don't even know what they don't know! Lately, this theory has been applied to people who question or refuse certain medical procedures. The mainstream believes that parents who would go against allopathic medical advice are simply so stupid that they don't even realize they don't understand how great mainstream actually is. Think about that. The only reason you'd prefer natural, is because you don't actually understand mainstream care. You aren't capable of reading or understanding science. You *think* you are, but it's only because you're so stupid that you're over-confident in your abilities. That's what they believe. How do you feel about that?
column34: Dunning- Dunning-Kruege Effect A phenomenon where, the less a person actually knows, the more confident they become in their knowledge/intelligence Earthley wellness

column31: AN APPLICATION FOR 2 CELL TOWERS DENIED BASED ON ENVIRONMENTAL AND HEALTH CONSIDERATION IN VIOLATION OF the infamous TELECOMMUNICATIONS ACT. Section 704 of the Telecommunications Act of 1996 took the power from states and municipalities to deny installations of cell towers based on environmental and health considerations, although the evidence of serious adverse health effects from the RF and microwave radiation emitted by these towers is clear. To a large extent, municipalities are correct when they say their hands are tied, but that is not a good enough reason to approve these towers. No one should be saying yes to a device knowing it may lead to serious injury and death. The mayor and city council of the city of Puna, Hawaii took a moral stance and denied application of two proposed cell phone towers quoting also health and environmental effects, including impact on bees. The vote was unanimous. One of the council members said, "We need to listen to the public, and I think today the public is speaking very clearly." The city council is aware that very likely it will be sued but made the morally correct decision. It is time to say NO if all municipalities will listen to its residents. Say NO and we will have a chance of stopping the insanity of 5G, and demand that this unlawful legislation be amended.

column31: It's the next in our series -- all about measles! Measles has been the subject of much debate, and a lot of it is due to the myths surrounding it. Hopefully, this helps clear some up. Measles has an incubation period of 7 - 21 days, averaging 10 - 12. It is NOT, contrary to popular belief, contagious until symptoms appear. (It *is* contagious prior to when the rash begins, there are 1 - 3 days of fever, cough, runny nose, and general flu-like symptoms before the rash appears.) A lot of kids will experience "complications" like diarrhea or ear infection, but these are generally mild. Serious complications are fairly rare, and more common in children with compromised immune systems. There's some evidence, on a population level, that measles infection seems to increase the risk of subsequent infections in the next several months, but no one really knows why. One large study in Britain showed that children who got measles were already more likely to visit the doctor/have sick days prior to measles infection, and were even more likely after. Some sort of underlying immune dysfunction may play a role in this. But, all studies have focused on population-level data and no one has examined individual cases or figured out what is really going on here. The measles vaccine was licensed in 1963. It is a live-virus vaccine. (The inactivated virus version wasn't effective in preventing measles, and many children ended up with atypical measles later, so it was never approved.) It was the measles portion of the vaccine that was potentially implicated in the now-infamous 1998 Wakefield study. That study was tiny, covering only 12 children, and looked at colitis diagnoses in children with autism. 8 of the mothers reported that their children's symptoms began after an MMR vaccine, and it was noted that the vaccine strain of measles was found in their bowels. Wakefield noted this in his research and recommended that follow-up studies be done to explore this correlation. He DID NOT conclude that vaccines caused autism and that was not the point of the study! Today, we still don't have solid data on the risks of the vaccine. We know there is DNA contamination in it, and this could cause DNA changes/damages. We know there are thousands and thousands of similar reports of chronic diarrhea, loss of speech and coordination, following the MMR. Proper studies aren't being done. We also know that any protection, once assumed to be life-long, wanes after 15 - 20 years, leaving adults (who are more likely to have complications) susceptible to infection. We also know that babies born to vaccinated mothers have a significantly lower duration of protection from maternal antibodies than babies born to naturally-immune mothers. This can shift disease burden to young infants, where it is also more serious. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26103708 https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/pubs/pinkbook/meas.html https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/67/wr/mm6740a3.htm https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2677258/ https://academic.oup.com/jid/article/206/10/1542/858893 https://www.bmj.com/content/362/bmj.k3976/rr-11 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26597262 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6231568/

column31: Birth control is a hot topic. Many women have looked to it as “freedom” to control their sexuality and their bodies. But others have experienced significant side effects from using hormonal contraception. So what’s the truth…is it the greatest invention ever, or should we exercise more caution? The mainstream literature, intended for patients, is pretty sparse. It promotes birth control, and notes “minor” risks for smokers, diabetics, or those with heart disease. Side effects are supposedly minor and uncommon. But the studies show a very different picture. First, the medical literature is heavily influenced by the beliefs of the researchers. Some studies blame contraceptives for all of women’s and the world’s problems; while others think they are a panacea that could be used to cure all kinds of disease. It’s hard to tease out the truth when there is so much inherent bias in the topic. What is sure, though, is that there are a lot more concerns with hormonal contraceptives than they tell women. Two risks in particular stand out. One is the changes to the brain. Several studies show that hormonal contraceptives influence memory, verbal ability, and spatial reasoning. A couple studies showed a positive effect, but some showed long-term negative effects. It’s clear that changing hormone balance has effects on the brain, and it needs to be studied more and women need to know about this. The second is the influence on metabolism. Several studies showed that “the pill” was pro-inflammatory, decreased insulin sensitivity, and increased the risk of developing type II diabetes. Even mainstream literature admits that in women who are already diabetic, starting “the pill” can raise blood sugar. In addition to these two risks, there’s some evidence that “the pill” can impact sexual functioning (many women have trouble with libido and arousal), as well as increasing the risk of some types of cancer and autoimmune disease. The news is not all bad. There is some evidence that birth control may lower the risk of other types of cancers, and reduce symptoms of some autoimmune diseases. The truth is, birth control – by design – impacts hormone balance. For some women, it may correct an ‘issue’ and improve things; for many others, it throws off normal hormone balance and makes things worse. There’s no way to say how exactly it will affect any specific woman. There are also many different forms and doses on the market, further complicating matters. Ideally, for just “birth control” needs, NFP (Natural Family Planning), or knowing your cycle and avoiding intercourse on fertile days or using a physical back-up method is safer than hormonal birth control, and done right, can work better, too. Some evidence shows that non-oral progesterone-only options may be slightly safer than combined options. (Patches, inserted rings.) For hormonal imbalances, look at underlying causes and consider food, herbs, and vitamin/mineral supplements to naturally correct them, rather than trying out synthetic hormones. Ultimately, it’s up to every woman to decide what works best for her – but she needs all the information in order to do it. column31: Our thoughts are with our friends in Maine tonight. Issue 1 hit the ballot today, and the public was allowed to vote -- for the first time -- on whether or not there should be religious and philosophical exemptions to vaccination. Unfortunately, they lost, about 70/30. We are angry. We are sad. We can only imagine how our friends who live in Maine feel. This battle was never about whether or not any individual should vaccinate. It was only about having the right to make your own decision, whatever that is. Allowing individuals, along with their chosen health care professionals, to look over the risks and benefits, and make a thoughtful choice. That's all. Of course, this battle was never about public health, either. The "Yes" crowd was winning on funding (donated from individuals and small businesses), and the "no" crowd maintained that they were independent. Until, of course, Merck and Pfizer swooped in and donated $500,000 just a few weeks before the election -- late enough that it didn't have to be declared until the vote was said and done. Why would pharmaceutical companies -- those who stand to profit off this -- jump in and donate so much money, if it's just about public health? It's clearly about them, and their power, and their revenue. It's time for us to stop asking for permission. This game is rigged against us, and we won't play anymore. We have just as much right to live freely on this planet as anyone else. No one gets to tell us what to do with our bodies, least of all those who stand to heavily profit off trying to force things. Time for civil disobedience. Enough is enough.

column31: This is satire. If we don't keep fighting for medical freedom, pretty soon something like this wouldn't be all that far-fetched. Kids would arrive at school, and immediately be asked to take their temperature with a disposable thermometer, write down any symptoms they have, if any family member has recently been ill, and other health metrics. That info could then be used to make sure that no one was in the classroom sick or asymptomatic but potentially able to spread disease. (If we're worried about keeping people healthy...!) Of course, in reality, requiring such info is invasive and ridiculous. We should certainly encourage people to stay home when sick, and enable them to do so (not penalizing them for missing days of school; not requiring a doctor's note; allowing them to make up work at home). We should certainly encourage regular hand-washing. But the rest of it? Leave peoples' personal health decisions alone. Or we'll soon live in a world where "personal" health decisions are public knowledge.

column31: Many states have or are trying to mandate prophylactic eye ointment for all newborns right now...but what is the evidence for this? This eye ointment, applied within minutes of birth -- erythromycin in the US -- is intended to prevent blindness caused by gonorrhea infection. If you do not have gonorrhea, your baby is not at risk. Many mothers are not told why it is used or whether or not their baby is at risk. This practice started in the late 1800s, when gonorrhea was common and blindness occurred frequently in newborns. A doctor began using silver nitrate at birth and blindness dropped significantly. If a mother has untreated gonorrhea, there is a 30 - 50% chance her baby will contract it. Premature babies, waters ruptured early in labor, sepsis during birth, maternal fever in labor and other factors increase the risk. If a baby does contract the infection, blindness can occur in as little as 24 hours. Gonorrhea often presents with non-specific symptoms and can be asymptomatic. This is why the mainstream treats every baby -- just in case. However, there are some risks associated with the eye ointment. Many other developed countries do not treat prophylactically and do not have higher rates of gonorrhea-induced conjunctivitis. Gonorrhea rates are increasing in the population, but many cases are antibiotic-resistant, and typical prophylaxis strategies may fail. Doctors may also recommend the ointment to protect against other forms of neonatal conjunctivitis, but there's not strong evidence that this is helpful, and the other causes don't typically lead to blindness or have serious complications. The bottom line? Informed choice. Many babies are not at risk and a blanket recommendation is not helpful or evidence-based. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4507834/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2795679/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6457593/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6240167/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4027342/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21534852 https://www.researchgate.net/publication/227524707_A_Meta-analysis_of_the_Efficacy_of_Ocular_Prophylactic_Agents_Used_for_the_Prevention_of_Gonococcal_and_Chlamydial_Ophthalmia_Neonatorum https://www.rxlist.com/ilotycin-side-effects-drug-center.htm https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6461120/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4135894/

column31: The truth is: we don't know. A lot of people are starting to run around the internet and say that it 'definitely' or 'likely' will cause a cytokine storm and kill people, and that you shouldn't use or recommend it. This is based on a few things. First, elderberry, when someone is sick, does increase pro-inflammatory cytokines. It's part of how it "boosts" the immune system to help your body heal itself. (It does not have the same action in healthy people, it's anti-inflammatory and modulating.) Second, from what little we know about CoVid-19, it heavily impacts the respiratory system, causing respiratory distress and pneumonia, which is what kills people. People have combined these two facts and have surmised that if a person with CoVid-19 is given elderberry, that it will increase the cytokines too much, lead to a cytokine storm, and cause death. Therefore, they recommend against it. But hang on. Although elderberry increases cytokines, there is no solid evidence that it has ever actually caused a cytokine storm or killed anyone this way. It's just theoretical right now. Some still may not want to take the risk, believing 'better safe than sorry....' Most of the people who have trouble with elderberry have underlying conditions. Some people with autoimmune conditions feel worse or experience flares when using elderberry. (Others actually feel better -- there's no blanket recommendation here.) Most of the people who are becoming seriously ill or dying from CoVid-19 have underlying conditions. It is possible that for someone with underlying conditions, who is already experiencing a lot of chronic inflammation, elderberry could be a 'tipping point' for them and could contribute to a cytokine storm. BUT we have no proof that this has happened yet. However, the situation for someone with underlying conditions, who is older and fragile, is not the same as someone who is young and healthy. We advise caution in someone in fragile health (and that is in general) and would use a lot of lung-supporting herbs, like mullein, as well as anti-inflammatory herbs like cinnamon or turmeric for respiratory symptoms. With young, healthy people, especially using elderberry as a general immune support rather than a remedy, we have no concerns. If we see any firm evidence that changes our stance, then we will update this and share the evidence. At this time, this is what we feel comfortable with.

column31: What is #HBOT? "Hyperbaric oxygen therapy (HBOT) is the medical use of oxygen in a pressurized environment, at a level higher than 1 atmosphere absolute (ATA). Increased pressure allows for oxygen to dissolve and saturate the blood plasma (independent of hemoglobin/red blood cells), which yields a broad variety of positive physiological, biochemical and cellular effects. This noninvasive therapy is the most trusted way to increase oxygen levels to all organs of the body. The typical treatment lasts for 60-90 minutes, during which the patient lies down and breathes normally. HBOT has been demonstrated in several clinical studies to enhance the body’s innate ability to repair and regenerate." Benefits of #HBOT: BENEFITS The Power of HBOT is in the Pressure. By pressurizing oxygen, we are able to raise blood and tissue oxygen levels in areas where they are reduced due to illness or injury. No other therapy can do that!
